items.sentence: Tom could've left three days ago, but he's still here.
If you go out so lightly dressed, you'll catch a cold.
It would be better if you stayed here a little longer.
I don't think that Tom knows when Mary came to Boston.
I don't think that Tom knows what Mary is doing today.
I suspect Tom and Mary need to do that sometime today.
I don't think that you need to tell Tom what Mary did.
You know both Tom and Mary want to do that, don't you?
When was the last time that you were really surprised?
Where were you the night that the factory burned down?
